                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>30 feet. Living creatures are frightened 1 while in a mummy pharaoh's despair aura. They can't naturally recover from this fear while in the area but recover instantly once they leave the area. When a creature first enters the area, it must succeed at a <span data-pf2-check=\"will\" data-pf2-dc=\"26\" data-pf2-traits=\"aura,divine,emotion,enchantment,fear,incapacitation,mental\" data-pf2-label=\"Great Despair DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Will</span> save (after taking the penalty from being frightened) or be paralyzed for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}. The creature is then temporarily immune for 24 hours.</p>"
